1.00	Stoner_criterion	Edmund Clifton Stoner	Electron bands can spontaneously split into up and down spins. This happens if the relative gain in exchange interaction (the interaction of electrons via the Pauli exclusion principle) is larger than the loss in kinetic energy.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8d/Stoner_model_of_ferromagnetism.svg/260px-Stoner_model_of_ferromagnetism.svg.png
